<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9063> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9063" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 750, footnote 346" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7220> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7220" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 78. Procos. 77. His province included both Transalpine and Cisalpine Gaul, since M. Iunius Brutus (52) was his legatus (Badian, Mel. Piganiol, 910; cf. MRR 2.91). Criniti dates his death in Sardinia in summer 77 (MIL 30, 4, 1969, 445). For a detailed study of Lepidus' career, see N. Criniti in MIL 30, 4, 1969, 319-459. On his quaestorship, probably ca. 91, see Badian, Klio 66, 1984, 300-301. Procos. or propr. in Sicily 80. In MRR 2.80, refer also to Cic. Verr. 2.2.8, and Shackleton Bailey, HSPh 83, 1979, 245-246.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4314> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4314" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul (Sall. Hist. 1.77.7M), assigned to Transalpine Gaul (App. BC 1.107). His insurrection and march on Rome were crushed near Rome in this year (see 78, Consuls). He then retreated in Etruria, and escaped to Sardinia, where he died (Sall. Hist. 1.74-83M; Liv. Per. 90; Val. Max. 2.8.7; Ascon. 19C; Plin. NH 7.122 and 186; Plut. Pomp. 16.1-6; App. BC 1.107; Flor. 2.11.5-8; Iul. Exup. 6; Ampel. 40.2; Oros. 5.22.16-18; of. Rut. Nam. 295-299). See 78, Consuls." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4280> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4280" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "CIL 12.2.588, 734-737; Cic. Balb. 34 and 39; Sall. Hist. 1.1M; Liv. Per. 90; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 56f., 130, 484f. (Lepidus' name entire; Q. Lut[ati]us Q. f. [Q. n.] Catulu[s]); Plin. NH 10.50; 35.13; 36.49 and 109; Eutrop. 6.1.1; Chr. 354 (Lepido et Catulo), so also Fast. Hyd., and Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod. Lepidus quarreled with his colleague, attempted to prevent giving funeral honors to Sulla, and, proposing a program to restore the powers of the tribunate, to carry new grain laws, and restore the confiscated lands to their former owners, began an insurrection, while Catulus became the leader of the opposing forces (Cic. Cat. 3.24; Sall. Hist. 1.54-73M; Liv. Per. 90; Suet. Iul. 3; Plut. Sull. 34.4-5; Pomp. 15.1-16.2; App. BC 1.105-107; Gran. Lic. 43-45B; Flor. 2.11.1-6; Dio 44.28.2, and 47.4, Iul. Exup. 6; Eutrop. 6.5.1; Oros. 5.22.16; Schol. Gron. 286 Stangl). Catulus also received charge of the restoration of the temple of Jupiter on the Capitolium (CIL 12.2.737-ILS 35; of. 35a; Cic. Verr. 2.4.69; see especially 62, Praetors, on Caesar)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4238> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4238" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "An oppressive governor of Sicily (Cic. Verr. 2.3.212; Ps.-Ascon. 187, and 259 Stangl, where he is termed Praetor)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4198> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4198" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 80, Promagistrates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4197> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4197" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "2 The latest date possible under the Cornelian law." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4170> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4170" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "No title preserved. The officer who captured Norba in late 82 or early 81 (App. BC 1.94)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3922> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3922" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "10 Cichorius' supplement is based on the space available, the ending of the name, the filiation and the tribe (RS 147)." .
